### LOCKED Phase 2 design decisions (no Q-decisions — settled today)

**8 new tables total.**

Grading model (5):
- `GradingScheme` — per-school, exactly one per school (`@@unique([schoolId])`).
- `GradingComponent` — N per scheme (CA1, CA2, Project, Exam, Practical…),
  each weight + label + order; weights MUST sum to 100, validated atomically
  at write.
- `GradeBoundary` — per-school letter↔range map; WAEC scale pre-seeded at
  school creation, editable. A1=75–100, B2=70–74, B3=65–69, C4=60–64,
  C5=55–59, C6=50–54, D7=45–49, E8=40–44, F9=0–39.
- `AssessmentScore` — one row per student×subject×term×component; STRICT
  validation: score ∈ [0, component.weight] (scores stored already-weighted).
- `Assessment` — denormalized summary student×subject×term; totalScore,
  letterGrade, classPosition, subjectPosition; materialized on write.

Attendance model (2):
- `AttendanceRecord` — daily, UNIVERSAL (no opt-in); one row per student×date;
  PRESENT/ABSENT/LATE/EXCUSED + markedBy/markedAt; upsert-the-day.
- `SubjectAttendanceRecord` — subject-period, SEPARATE table, OPT-IN via
  `School.subjectAttendanceEnabled` (boolean added in slice 8 alongside the
  table). status + markedBy/markedAt + subjectId + period.

Report card model (1):
- `ReportCard` — MATERIALIZED artifact (not live-rendered); one row per
  student×term; PDF via Puppeteer/headless-Chrome → R2, `artifactUrl` on row;
  BullMQ batch render at term end. HYBRID approval: granular per-(student×
  subject) subject-teacher sign-off (recommended shape = two columns on
  `Assessment`, NOT a separate table — keeps us at 8) + batch per-(arm×term)
  form-teacher review → principal approval → release. States: DRAFT →
  SUBJECT_REVIEWED → FORM_REVIEWED → PRINCIPAL_APPROVED → RELEASED (arm
  advances as a unit; reopen is audited). Comments at 3 grains — subjectComment
  (Assessment), formTeacherComment (ReportCard, per student-term), principalNote
  (ReportCard, per arm-term) — manual text in Phase 2, AI-hook-ready for Phase 5
  (plain text columns, no AI-specific schema).

